Strong climate action will save our planet, but we still need resilient infrastructure to protect coastal communities from higher tides &amp; extreme weather that’s already in store. 

@IGSD_DC says we need $400 billion over the next 20 years to make it happen. 

Better get moving.

A federal report “unheeded”; “weaknesses in the system we haven't dealt with”; 45,000 megawatts of generation offline;
 an electric grid “ill-equipped for these weather events”; and the fossil-fuel-funded politicos blame renewables.
